[1
Date: Wed 15 Aug 2001 10:35:12 +0100
From: Pablo Nart <P.Nart@vet.gla.ac.uk>
Source: Associated Press Worldstream, Tue 14 Aug 2001 [edited

Number of Dengue Fever Cases Increases in Vietnam
-------------------------------------------------
HANOI: The number of cases of dengue fever is rising rapidly in Vietnam as
the disease nears the peak of a 3-4 year cycle, an official said on Tue 14
Aug 2001. As of 8 Aug 2001, a total of 18 674 people have contracted dengue
fever this year, an increase of 51 percent over the same period last year,
the Ministry of Health official said. Of these, 44 people died, 13 more
than last year.
Most of the cases were reported in Vietnam's 19 southern provinces, where
tropical conditions provide an ideal environment for [spread of the
mosquito-borne disease. A second round of an anti-dengue campaign will be
launched later this month, targeting the southern provinces, the official
said.
The practice of people in southern Vietnam of storing rain water in
containers for later use provides a good breeding ground for mosquitoes. In
1999, the government launched a program to fight the disease with an annual
budget of 15 billion dong (1 million dollars). The program has helped
reduce the number of people contracting dengue fever. Nearly 400 people
died from dengue in 1998, the year before the program's launch.
