[2
Date: Wed 15 Aug 2001 10:35:12 +0100
From: Pablo Nart <P.Nart@vet.gla.ac.uk>
Source: Philippine Daily Inquirer, PDI Southern Luzon Bureau, Sun 12 Aug
2001 [edited

17 Dengue Fever Deaths in Batangas, the Philippines
---------------------------------------------------
BATANGAS CITY: The provincial government is set to declare the province
under a state of [emergency in the face of an upsurge of dengue cases that
has killed 17 people and afflicted [hospitalised? 217 others. Provincial
Health Officer Dr. Isagani Bolompo said 19 towns, including the cities of
Lipa, Tanauan, and Batangas, had been seriously affected by dengue fever.
Bolompo said the number of cases was expected to rise when reports from
public and private hospitals and health centers [have been collated. Most
of those who died were from Lipa and Tanauan. The rest were from Bauan, San
Pascual, and San Jose towns. Other towns affected by the disease are Mataas
na Kahoy, Mabini, Lemery, Rosario, Ibaan, Balayan, Tuy, Nasugbu, Calaca,
Taal, Padre Garcia, Taysan, Lobo, San Juan, and Cuenca.
The incidence of dengue fever has alarmed local health officials since
January. Late last month, the provincial council proposed to place the
whole province under a state of [emergency. The Center for Health
Development of the regional Department of Health said the current situation
has surpassed the 423 dengue cases reported in 1998 and 368 in 1999.
Bolompo has requested PHP 10 million from the provincial government to fund
the Dengue Prevention and Control Program. The provincial government has
PHP 32 million in reserve funds for [emergency assistance.
[Byline: Mei Magsino
