[3
Date: Wed 15 Aug 2001 10:35:12 +0100
From: Pablo Nart <P.Nart@vet.gla.ac.uk>
Source: Xinhua (via COMTEX), Wed 8 Aug 2001 [edited

Total of Dengue Cases in the Philippines approaches 8000
---------------------------------------------------------
MANILA: Dengue fever cases in the Philippines have increased to 7940 so far
this year with 69 reported deaths, official figures show. Most of the cases
belonged to the 1-9 years age group. Deaths were highest among those less
than one year old and those aged over 40. The National Capital Region had
the highest number of cases with 1614, followed by Central Visayas with
1571 and Central Luzon with 1137.
There is no ongoing outbreak now and all previously reported outbreaks have
been contained, Health Secretary Manuel Dayrit stated on Wed 8 Aug 2001,
adding that the elimination of mosquito larvae and mosquito breeding sites
is one of the best strategies in controlling the population of
dengue-carrier mosquitoes.
